'''Aaron Landes''' (November 1, 1929 – April 19, 2014) was an American rabbi in the Conservative movement and a rear admiral in the United States Naval Reserve. He served as rabbi of [[Beth Sholom Congregation (Elkins Park, Pennsylvania)|Beth Sholom Congregation]] in [[Elkins Park, Pennsylvania]] for 36 years.<ref name=Exponent>{{cite web |url=http://www.jewishexponent.com/community/2014/04/rabbi-aaron-landes-prominent-leader-and-naval-chaplain-dies-at-84 |title=Rabbi Aaron Landes, Prominent Leader and Naval Chaplain, Dies at 84 |last=Elkin |first=Michael |date=April 20, 2014 |work=Jewish Exponent |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref> With his wife, Sora Eisenberg Landes, he founded the Forman Hebrew Day School, now known as the Forman branch of the Perelman Jewish Day School.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haaretz.com/jewish-world/jewish-world-news/1.587064 |title=Rabbi Aaron Landes, longtime Naval Reserve chaplains chief, dies |author=JTA |date=April 24, 2014 |work=[[Haaretz]] |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref> He also was instrumental in founding the [[Hebrew Free Loan Society of Greater Philadelphia]].<ref name=Exponent />

Born in 1929 in Revere, Massachusetts,<ref>http://obits.dignitymemorial.com/dignity-memorial/obituary.aspx?n=Aaron-Landes&lc=0361&pid=170795460&mid=5944717</ref> Landes served in the [[United States Navy]] for two years after his ordination and continued in the [[United States Navy Reserve]] until 1989, reaching the rank of [[Rear admiral (United States)|Rear Admiral]] and retiring as head of the Chaplain Corps. During his naval career, he was instrumental in the building of Jewish chapels at the [[United States Naval Academy]] in [[Annapolis, Maryland]], and at the Naval Base in [[Norfolk, Virginia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.philly.com/1989-07-05/news/26133526_1_jewish-chapel-first-rabbi-synagogue |title=Rabbi Admiral Retires From Naval Reserve Beth Sholom Head Retires As Chaplain |last=Avery |first=Ron |date=July 5, 1989 |work=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]] |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jewsingreen.com/2014/04/rabbi-aaron-landes-radm-ret-zl/ |title=Rabbi Aaron Landes, RADM (Ret) Z"L |author=JR |date=April 20, 2014 |work=jewsingreen.com |accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref>

